                <h1>Understanding Form OF-306: A Key to Federal Employment</h1>
                <p>Form OF-306 is not a background check itself; rather, it's a declaration of employment and personal history used by federal agencies during the hiring process. This form helps employers gather information about potential employees, ensuring they meet necessary qualifications and do not have disqualifying issues. Understanding its role can clarify the hiring process.</p>
